						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Climate-change/Related-developments/Indigenous-lands-protected-areas-and-slowing-climate-change" title="Indigenous lands, protected areas, and slowing climate change" alt="link">Indigenous lands, protected areas, and slowing climate change</a></h2>

	
					<p>A collaborative study between forest scientists from 13 organizations, universities and research institutions makes specific recommendations for incorporating indigenous lands and other protected areas into strategies to reduce emissions from deforestation and forest degradation. It concludes that strengthening support for indigenous lands and other protected areas is a “win-win” situation: it could mitigate climate change while securing the planet’s natural and cultural heritage. (Source: PLoS Biology, 16 March 2010)</p>
