					<p>In this radio programme native peoples from the Arctic and the Amazon to Pacific islands testify to what is happening to them, as seas and temperatures continue to rise disrupting their ancestral livelihoods. Their responses to these changes offer much-needed guidance about how to develop the resilience and inventiveness that are essential to humanity’s long-term survival. (Source: Traditional Knowledge Bulletin, February 2010)</p>
